CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 11, 1941, pg. 9, reads: "Mrs. Agnes Curry, seated before cake, as she appeared at the celebration of her 94th birthday, Wednesday. She is surrounded by fond relatives and friends at the home of her grand-niece, Mrs. Eva Reese in Monticello street.  Seated: Miss Willa Curry, Mrs. Ruth White, Mrs. Agnes Curry, Mrs. McDaniel. Standing: Mrs. Lillian Lloyd, Mrs. Ella Harris, Mrs. Jane Madison, Mrs. Alise Smith, Mrs. Eva Reese."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of nine women, some elderly, including Willa Curry, Ruth White, Mrs. McDaniel, Lillian Lloyd, Ella Mae "Olga" Harris, Jane Madison, Alise Smith, and Eva Reese, gathered for 94th birthday of Agnes Curry seated behind cake, in Reese home on Monticello Street
